Package intervals

Class Functions

  • java.lang.Object
    • intervals.Functions

  • public class Functions
extends java.lang.Object
    defines interval valued functions, using a functional interface, thanks to the Function object all the functions here defined take one interval as an orgument, and outputs one interval: this is the interval version of real valued, one variable mathematical functions. most usual functions are defined in this class, from trigonometric, to hyperbolic and exponential functions
    Author:
    gabriel
